ES 150/EN 101X

Hello everyone and happy fall! I hope your summer gave you a chance to recharge and reset. This coming academic year 2026-2027 we are entering our second year of departmental assessment. For us, assessing where our students are helps us learn more about what we’re doing well as a department as well as where we can make adjustments. All of this helps us reach our shared goals of best serving our students, and how we do that should naturally be data informed! 

In AY 2025-2026, we assessed this learning outcome:

Program Learning Outcome #1: Read and engage critically with a diverse range of texts and perspectives   

One of the key takeaways we got from this process was that sending information out sooner should help with more participation, and the more of us that are involved, the more we can learn and grow.

This year, we will assess this learning outcome:

Program Learning Outcome #3:** **Critically evaluate and integrate evidence to develop an argument ** ** 

Here is what that looks like for you.

August 1: Receive notice of this year’s outcome, the rubric we will use to score artifacts, and instructions

Periodically throughout the fall semester: receive reminders to submit artifacts 

End of fall semester: attend portfolio scoring session 

Spring semester: